trailingComments.value: Playfab has a size limit of 10k bytes per key. Swarmsim's passed that before. We can update 10 keys per push for a limit of 100k, which is enough.
encode and decode are not symmetric! They match Playfab's (asymmetric) api:
encode returns/set accepts {foo: 'bar'}, but decode accepts/get returns {foo: {Value: 'bar'}}
